@Jennifer88huang thanks for information about how and when to use third and second person in technical writing.

In regards to "Functions" vs "functions", after examining Azure documentation in more detail, it uses capital "f" in "functions" when they are referring to the name of the product i.e. "Azure Functions" or "Durable Functions".  It uses a lower case "f" for "function" when referring to a general or common concept. "Serverless functions" is not a brand name, it is the term for a general concept/framework, thus I think it is spelled with a lower case "f".  

I think its reasonable for us spell Pulsar Functions with a capital "f", when we are referring to this specific product/framework.  We can use the lower case "functions", when we refer to general concept of a function e.g. math function

